title: Top travel photos of the week
text:
Top travel photos of the week Last updated 09:39, October 9 2015 REUTERS/LUCAS JACKSON JACKY NAEGELEN/REUTERS SHAMIL ZHUMATOV/REUTERS LUCAS JACKSON/Reuters REUTERS/Toru Hanai TOBY MELVILLE/REUTERS ChinaFotoPress/Getty Images Vince Caligiuri/Getty Images NAVESH CHITRAKAR FABRIZIO BENSCH/REUTERS AMIT DAVE/Reuters 
A rainbow forms after a passing rain shower near Grants, New Mexico. 
The leaves of a tree have partially changed to display its autumn colors near the Eiffel Tower in Paris, France. 
Children pose for their parents on a rock in front of the Bolshoy (Big) Almaty lake at 2,600 (8530 ft) meters above sea level at a sunny autumn day in a mountains outside Almaty, Kazakhstan. 
A woman and child take a photograph as hot air balloons lift off during the 2015 Albuquerque International Balloon Fiesta in Albuquerque, New Mexico. 
Japan's Mount Fuji, surrounded by cloud, is seen from an airplane. Mount Fuji, at 3,776 metres (12,388 ft) is Japan's highest mountain. 
A passenger plane is seen with the moon behind over west London, Britain. 
Tourists visit the Huangguoshu Waterfalls during the National Day holiday in Anshun, Guiyang Province of China. Many scenic spots in China have welcomed the tourism peak during the 7-day National Day holiday. 
Who Shot Thebarman from the Chris Waller stable walks through the shallow waters during a trackwork session at Altona Beach. 
A girl feeds pigeons at Hanumandhoka Durbar Square in Kathmandu, Nepal. 
People look at an illuminated light installation called "House of Cards" during a technical check for the Festival of Lights in Berlin. 
Women dressed in traditional attire pose after taking part in rehearsals for the "garba" dance ahead of Navratri festival in Ahmedabad, India. Navratri, held in honour of Hindu Goddess Durga, is celebrated over a period of nine days where thousands of youths dance the night away in traditional costumes. 1 of 11 
Here is our round up of the top travel photos from around the world. 
Do you have a favourite? Let us know in the comments. Ad Feedback Vince Caligiuri/Getty Images
